dataStructure.name: sid.org.tmforum.tip.resource.res.log.proto.DeviceHybridRoutingDetails
dataStructure.description:
This association defines the set of HybridRoutingProtocols that are currently being used on this LogicalDevice. The supportsProtocol aggregation is used to determine if a particular Protocol (not just a HybridRoutingProtocol) is supported by this LogicalDevice. The particular semantics of this association are defined by the DeviceHybridRoutingDetails association class.

This association class is optional
dataStructure.label: DeviceHybridRoutingDetails
